09/10/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The United States will give additional military aid in amount of $3m to Bulgaria, following a recent decision by the US Congress, according to a defence ministry announcement Friday (October 6th). 
The money would be allocated to specific projects after consultations between the ministry and the US Embassy in Sofia.
In other news Friday, parliament approved a government proposal to deploy the 160-crew military frigate "Drazki" with the UN Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL). 
During its two-month mission, the "Drazki" will conduct patrol duties. 
(Monitor - 07/10/06; Mediapool - 06/10/06)
